eir families and friends  Box lunches will be provided to all cadets  as well as for those family members who purchased tickets on Matriculation Day from the Parents Council Those who did not buy tickets on Matriculation Day for box lunches may purchase food in New Market or bring their own picnic lunch  The events at New Market conclude with a parade through the town after lunch  Cadets must return to Post on the buses  but will be able to sign out to spend time that evening with their parents in Lexington All new cadets must return to post no later than 10 00 p m  More information about New Market Battlefield State Park VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 